<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="39" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39">
This species is known from Minas Gerais, Brazil (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3852/mycologia.97.6.1348" author="Arruda, MCC" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" pagination="1378 - 1361" refId="B5" refString="Arruda, MCC, Sepuvelda, GF, Miller, RNG, Ferreira, MASV, Santiago, DVR, Resende, MLV, Dianese, JC, Felipe, MSS, 2005. Crinipellis brasiliensis, a new species based on morphological and molecular data. Mycologia 97: 1378 - 1361, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3852/mycologia.97.6.1348" title="Crinipellis brasiliensis, a new species based on morphological and molecular data." url="https://doi.org/10.3852/mycologia.97.6.1348" volume="97" year="2005">Arruda et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="39" type="observations">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Observations.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Niveiro, Lodge &amp; Aime" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Arruda, G. F. Sepulveda, R. N. G. Miller, M. A. Ferreira &amp; M. S. Felipe" baseAuthorityYear="2020" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Moniliophthora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Moniliophthora brasiliensis" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Moniliophthora brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by the light pink to crimson red pileus surface, ellipsoidal basidiospores, 10-14 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5-7 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, and lageniform cheilocystidia, with a thin apex, 28-37 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
10-16 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
in size (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3852/mycologia.97.6.1348" author="Arruda, MCC" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" pagination="1378 - 1361" refId="B5" refString="Arruda, MCC, Sepuvelda, GF, Miller, RNG, Ferreira, MASV, Santiago, DVR, Resende, MLV, Dianese, JC, Felipe, MSS, 2005. Crinipellis brasiliensis, a new species based on morphological and molecular data. Mycologia 97: 1378 - 1361, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3852/mycologia.97.6.1348" title="Crinipellis brasiliensis, a new species based on morphological and molecular data." url="https://doi.org/10.3852/mycologia.97.6.1348" volume="97" year="2005">Arruda et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Niveiro, Lodge &amp; Aime" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Arruda, G. F. Sepulveda, R. N. G. Miller, M. A. Ferreira &amp; M. S. Felipe" baseAuthorityYear="2020" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Moniliophthora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Moniliophthora brasiliensis" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Moniliophthora brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a parasite of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malpighiaceae" genus="Heteropterys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Heteropterys acutifolia" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acutifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Heteropterys acutifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malpighiaceae" genus="Heteropterys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Malpighiaceae</taxonomicName>
). Only ITS sequence data are available for this taxon, which was derived from a dikaryotic basidiome collected from a necrotic broom on 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. acutifolia" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" rank="species" species="acutifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">H. acutifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3852/mycologia.97.6.1348" author="Arruda, MCC" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" pagination="1378 - 1361" refId="B5" refString="Arruda, MCC, Sepuvelda, GF, Miller, RNG, Ferreira, MASV, Santiago, DVR, Resende, MLV, Dianese, JC, Felipe, MSS, 2005. Crinipellis brasiliensis, a new species based on morphological and molecular data. Mycologia 97: 1378 - 1361, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3852/mycologia.97.6.1348" title="Crinipellis brasiliensis, a new species based on morphological and molecular data." url="https://doi.org/10.3852/mycologia.97.6.1348" volume="97" year="2005">Arruda et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Niveiro, Lodge &amp; Aime" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Arruda, G. F. Sepulveda, R. N. G. Miller, M. A. Ferreira &amp; M. S. Felipe" baseAuthorityYear="2020" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Moniliophthora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Moniliophthora brasiliensis" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Moniliophthora brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is extremely similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. perniciosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" rank="species" species="perniciosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">M. perniciosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and diagnosis between the two species at present is based soley on differences in ITS sequence data (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3852/mycologia.97.6.1348" author="Arruda, MCC" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" pagination="1378 - 1361" refId="B5" refString="Arruda, MCC, Sepuvelda, GF, Miller, RNG, Ferreira, MASV, Santiago, DVR, Resende, MLV, Dianese, JC, Felipe, MSS, 2005. Crinipellis brasiliensis, a new species based on morphological and molecular data. Mycologia 97: 1378 - 1361, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3852/mycologia.97.6.1348" title="Crinipellis brasiliensis, a new species based on morphological and molecular data." url="https://doi.org/10.3852/mycologia.97.6.1348" volume="97" year="2005">Arruda et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
